704263f-b.title: Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Caton Avenue
704263f-b.text:
Flatbush Ave., east side, at the foot of Caton Ave. In the
left foreground is a trolley right of way swinging in to Flatbush
Ave. The turret top building in backoaround was rased in July 1929.
The building at right facing on Flatbush Ave was razed in 1930 and
Caton Ave. extended. It was tue Pome of W. StootlEoff; in 1891
was the property of Schoomker; in 1924 John Reis was owner. It
housed the Kings County Rural Gazette in 1873.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing Nas. 805-815 Flatbush Ave., looking southward
from Lenox Ave. Seen are the Flatbush Ave. trolley lines.
October, 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
